<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
(ASCII mode) Nether mists in Nether Realm are plain yellow (as if they weren't in LoS), but after using Clairvoyance or !oEnlightement they attain their cool violet blinking look (and by the way LoS for terrain is greatly increased). It seems that code for FORGET dungeon flag in the Void or Nether Realm causes "you don't see any terrain features". <p>
I think that 'light up the whole dungeon' effect upon entering each level of these dungeons would fix the problem, not affecting gameplay (because monsters, items, stairs are always visible as if in full LoS). <a class="badinterwiki" title="Update" href="./InterWiki">no</a>, it wouldn't - destruction effects restore 'bad' state of visibility. 
</p>
